comments.body:
nit:
To make it slightly more readable:
```
CTxDestination dest;
switch (script_type) {
    case ScriptType::P2WPKH: dest = WitnessV0KeyHash(pubkey); break;
    case ScriptType::P2TR:   dest = WitnessV1Taproot(XOnlyPubKey{pubkey}); break;
    default: assert(false);
}
scriptPubKey = GetScriptForDestination(dest);
```

Also, I'm surprised we don't have any visitor class or utility function that receives the script type + data and retrieves the destination or the script. It seems something we should be doing in several places.

